New Records: This was the first time since 2011 that Ireland has come from behind to win away from home.
Key Match Events: Robbie Brady scored a late winner in the 88th minute to secure a 2-1 victory for the Republic of Ireland.
Liam Scales scored his first international goal to equalize for Ireland in the 57th minute.
Joel Pohjanpalo scored for Finland in the 17th minute.
Robbie Brady had a goal disallowed due to the ball going out of play.
